# Architecture & monorepo boundaries

```
apps/web/          Next.js 15 UI + API routes + server actions
packages/contracts Zod schemas — every cross-boundary artifact
packages/db        Drizzle schema, migrations, ownership scoping
packages/engine    Pure pipeline — NO Next.js/React imports
packages/adapters  Broker adapters (paper, Alpaca, Kalshi, Polymarket, …)
packages/llm       Provider clients + schema-locked call wrappers + budgets
```

## Authority model

- UI reads projections; writes only via validated, Clerk-scoped APIs
- Model tiers emit schema-validated artifacts; **never submit orders**
- Deterministic core is the **only** layer calling broker trading endpoints
- Cross-tier artifacts travel in `HandoffEnvelope`

## Implementation rules

- Stack choices: `agent-docs/research/tech-decisions.md` (TD-nn) — log before substituting
- DB: ownership-scoping helpers on every query; append-only tables never updated/deleted
  (`action_traces`, `verification_records`, `credit_ledger`, `assistant_edits`)
- Queue: Postgres SKIP LOCKED pattern (`architecture/job-orchestration.md`)
- Env: `DATABASE_URL` standard; `.env.example` synced with `packages/contracts`
- Rate limiting: **admission-based call budgets**, never context truncation

## Domain quick map

- **Company** = user's canvas unit (philosophy, policies, seed, paper|live)
- **Modules** = research, data (library/live API), trend, trading presets, utilities
- **Module links** = real data-flow contracts on canvas edges

Full detail: `architecture/system-architecture.md`, `architecture/data-model.md`.
